            "to",
            "travel",
            "this",
            "summer?"
          ],
          "correct": "Are they going to travel this summer?"
        },
        {
          "prompt": "I'll call you tomorrow (promise):",
          "words": [
            "I",
            "will",
            "call",
            "you",
            "tomorrow"
          ],
          "correct": "I will call you tomorrow"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "m3-ch4-quiz",
    "type": "quiz",
    "title": "Quiz: Future with Will and Going To",
    "description": "Test your mastery of the future.",
    "props": {
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "q1",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "\"The phone's ringing!\" — \"I ___ get it.\" (spontaneous)",
          "options": [
            "'m going to",
            "'ll",
            "going to",
            "shall"
          ],
          "correct": 1,
          "explanation": "Spontaneous decision → I'll."
        },
        {
          "id": "q2",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "\"We ___ visit Paris next month.\" (already planned)",
          "options": [
            "will",
            "'re going to",
            "won't",
            "shall"
          ],
          "correct": 1,
          "explanation": "Already planned → we're going to."
        },
        {
          "id": "q3",
          "type": "fill-blank",
          "question": "\"I think she ___ (pass) the exam.\" (opinion)",
          "correct": "will pass",
          "explanation": "Opinion/belief → will pass."
        },
        {
          "id": "q4",
          "type": "fill-blank",
          "question": "\"Look at those clouds! It ___ (rain)!\" (evidence)",
          "correct": "is going to rain",
          "explanation": "Evidence → is going to rain."
        },
        {
          "id": "q5",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "\"Don't worry, I ___ help you.\" (promise)",
          "options": [
            "'m going to",
            "'ll",
            "going to",
            "am"
          ],
          "correct": 1,
          "explanation": "Promise → I'll."
        },
        {
          "id": "q6",
          "type": "fill-blank",
          "question": "\"She ___ (not/come) to the party.\" (won't)",
          "correct": "won't come",
          "explanation": "Won't + base verb."
        },
        {
          "id": "q7",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "\"___ you be at the meeting tomorrow?\"",
          "options": [
            "Are",
            "Will",
            "Do",
            "Going"
          ],
          "correct": 1,
          "explanation": "Will you be...?"
        },
        {
          "id": "q8",
          "type": "fill-blank",
          "question": "\"I ___ travel this summer.\" (negative with going to)",
          "correct": "isn't going to",
          "explanation": "He isn't going to travel."
        },
        {
          "id": "q9",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "\"___ I close the door?\" (suggestion)",
          "options": [
            "Will",
            "Going to",
            "Shall",
            "Do"
          ],
          "correct": 2,
          "explanation": "Shall I...? = suggestion."
        },
        {
          "id": "q10",
          "type": "multiple-choice",
          "question": "Which sentence is correct?",
          "options": [
            "They're going to travel.",
            "They will to travel.",
            "They going to travel.",
            "They're going travel."
          ],
          "correct": 0,
          "explanation": "They're going to travel — correct form. (Not: will to, They going without 'are', or missing 'to')"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
